s precipitated in near-equilibrium with seawater and allows accurate estimation of seawater Sr/Ca ratios and carbon isotopic composition. In contrast, shell precipitation along lateral margins is dominantly controlled by metabolic activity, and calcite chemistry is not in equilibrium with ambient seawater. In this context, we present a biomineralization model where variations in skeletal Sr/ Ca and ??13C values are explained in the context of mantle metabolic activity and seawater salinity.},
