 Absolute Salinity Anomaly results in a standard error in SA of 0.0107 g kg−1. Using our algorithm for  SA reduces the error to 0.0048 g kg−1, reducing the mean square error by a factor of five. The number of sea 216 water samples used to develop the correlation relationship is limited, and we hope that the algorithm and error can be improved as further data becomes available.},
author = {{McDougall  D.R.; Millero, F.J.}, J.M; D R Jackett},
