–4 , genuinely reflect decoupling between CO 2 and climate or are an artefact associated with the difficulties of accurately reconstructing these critical features of Earth's history 13 . However, evidence for brief (typically {\textless} 1 Myr) cool pulses punctuating generally warm Jurassic and Cretaceous climates is challenging the prevailing high CO 2 Mesozoic 'greenhouse world' paradigm 3 indicated by palaeosols 5},
