trient utilization and mixing$\backslash$nwithin the upper water column. Because surface pCO(2) (at 0 m water$\backslash$ndepth) is always lower than at deeper depths and if the application of a$\backslash$nconstant K-D is valid, our results suggest that the polar North Atlantic$\backslash$nhas remained a CO2 sink during the calcification seasons of N.$\backslash$npachyderma (s) over the last deglaciation.},
