less}/inf{\textgreater}. Our finding may remove one potential source of uncertainty in $\delta$11B based pH reconstructions and provide us with greater confidence in our ability to reconstruct pH in the ancient oceans from at least some recrystallized foraminiferal calcite. However, further investigations should extend this approach to test the robustness of our findings across a range of taphonomies, ages and burial settings. {\textcopyright} 2015 The Authors.},
author = {Edgar, K M and Anagnostou, E and Pearson, P N and Foster, G L},
