nd on the range of settling velocity classes included in the estimate. If only SV classes settling at {\textgreater}50 m/d are included, the range of SVs at MedFlux was 214-298 m/d, with average mean value 242 m/d and standard deviation 31 m/d. These mean-velocity results are in excellent agreement with benchmark estimates of signal propagation velocities at Medflux (220??65 m/d); they are also well within the range of other recent benchmark studies. The agreement between the benchmark estimates and mean settling velocity estimates at MedFlux, but not with modal velocities, argues that the benchmark method estimates mean settling velocities. ?? 2009 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.},
